<paragraph id="E34236D4BC4AFFD851B9BF7DFE28F8B5" blockId="12.[151,1436,1582,2041]" pageId="12" pageNumber="35">
Comments: According to the original description, the specimens of this species studied by Lepeletier were collected in “Capitainerie de Goyan”, currently 
<collectingRegion id="2139F836BC4AFFD853CFBF91FC92F921" box="[689,815,1690,1717]" country="Brazil" name="Goias" pageId="12" pageNumber="35">Goiás state</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="9BEA7644BC4AFFD85245BF91FCC2F920" box="[827,895,1690,1716]" name="Brazil" pageId="12" pageNumber="35">Brazil</collectingCountry>
<materialsCitation id="53953C89BC4AFFD852F9BF91FE2CF8B5" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="2270703888" collectionCode="MNHP, OUMNH" location="Some" pageId="12" pageNumber="35" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Goias">
and they were housed at 
<collectionCode id="85ECAE11BC4AFFD855E0BF90FB4DF921" box="[1182,1264,1691,1717]" country="USA" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/3kvn-7rck" name="Princeton University" pageId="12" pageNumber="35">MNHP</collectionCode>
. Unfortunately, there was not found any specimen under this name in that collection or in 
<collectionCode id="85ECAE11BC4AFFD8528EBFB5FBE7F94C" box="[1008,1114,1726,1752]" pageId="12" pageNumber="35">OUMNH</collectionCode>
that could be recognized as primary 
<typeStatus id="3C468876BC4AFFD85189BFE8FE96F969" box="[247,299,1763,1789]" pageId="12" pageNumber="35">type</typeStatus>
. 
<location id="E622600FBC4AFFD85048BFE9FECBF968" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:6B5487C2BC4AFFD851E9BC95FAB9F86C:E622600FBC4AFFD85048BFE9FECBF968" box="[310,374,1762,1788]" name="Some" pageId="12" pageNumber="35" stateProvince="Goias">Some</location>
females of 
<taxonomicName id="24FD4D57BC4AFFD85087BFE8FDD6F968" authorityName="Lepeletier" authorityYear="1841" box="[505,619,1762,1789]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bicolor">
<emphasis id="D189EAC6BC4AFFD85087BFE8FDB1F969" box="[505,524,1763,1789]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="35">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="D189EAC6BC4AFFD85364BFE9FDD6F968" box="[538,619,1762,1788]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="35">bicolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
found at 
<collectionCode id="85ECAE11BC4AFFD853A9BFE8FC9AF969" box="[727,807,1763,1789]" country="USA" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/3kvn-7rck" name="Princeton University" pageId="12" pageNumber="35">MNHP</collectionCode>
were collected before the description of the species and none from 
<collectingRegion id="2139F836BC4AFFD8506CBE0DFE2CF8B5" box="[274,401,1798,1825]" country="Brazil" name="Goias" pageId="12" pageNumber="35">Goiás state</collectingRegion>
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E34236D4BC4AFFD851B9BE21FAB9F86C" blockId="12.[151,1436,1582,2041]" pageId="12" pageNumber="35">
The yellowish pilosity on the laterosuperior surface of the mesosoma mentioned by 
<bibRefCitation id="876C4B25BC4AFFD855DFBE21FADAF8D0" author="Lepeletier, A. L. M." box="[1185,1383,1834,1860]" pageId="12" pageNumber="35" refId="ref10183" refString="Lepeletier, A. L. M. (1841) Histoire Naturelle des Insectes. Hymenopteres. Vol. 2. Roret, Paris, 680 pp." type="book" year="1841">Lepeletier (1841)</bibRefCitation>
that contrasts with the black hairs of the rest of the body allows identifying this species and separating it from 
<taxonomicName id="24FD4D57BC4AFFD8543DBE44FE98F818" authority="Friese, 1899" authorityName="Friese" authorityYear="1899" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lutea">
<emphasis id="D189EAC6BC4AFFD8543DBE44FAEBF8FD" box="[1347,1366,1871,1897]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="35">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="D189EAC6BC4AFFD8541ABE45FA21F8FC" box="[1380,1436,1870,1896]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="35">lutea</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="876C4B25BC4AFFD851E9BE79FE98F818" author="Friese, H." box="[151,293,1906,1932]" pageId="12" pageNumber="35" pagination="39 - 48" refId="ref9884" refString="Friese, H. (1899 [1900]) Neue arten der Bienengattungen Epicharis Klug und Centris Fabr. Termeszetrajzi Fuzetek, 23, 39 - 48." type="journal article" year="1899">Friese, 1899</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. This latter species has a similar pattern of pubescence, although the yellow hairs are restricted to the mesoscutum and mesoscutellum, not extending to the lateral surface of the mesosoma as in 
<taxonomicName id="24FD4D57BC4AFFD855EBBE9CFABBF824" authorityName="Lepeletier" authorityYear="1841" box="[1173,1286,1942,1969]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bicolor">
<emphasis id="D189EAC6BC4AFFD855EBBE9CFB15F825" box="[1173,1192,1943,1969]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="35">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="D189EAC6BC4AFFD855CBBE9DFABBF824" box="[1205,1286,1942,1968]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="35">bicolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This species was correctly interpreted by 
<bibRefCitation id="876C4B25BC4AFFD850A9BEB1FD7FF840" author="Silveira, F. A. &amp; Melo, G. A. R. &amp; Almeida, E. A. B." box="[471,706,1978,2005]" pageId="12" pageNumber="35" refId="ref11263" refString="Silveira, F. A., Melo, G. A. R. &amp; Almeida, E. A. B. (2002) Abelhas brasileiras Sistematica e Identificacao. Fundacao Araucaria, Belo Horizonte, 254 pp." type="book" year="2002">
Silveira 
<emphasis id="D189EAC6BC4AFFD8534BBEB0FDDAF840" box="[565,615,1978,2004]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="35">et al</emphasis>
. (2002)
</bibRefCitation>
. 
<taxonomicName id="24FD4D57BC4AFFD853B3BEB0FCCAF840" authorityName="Lepeletier" authorityYear="1841" box="[717,887,1978,2005]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bicolor">
<emphasis id="D189EAC6BC4AFFD853B3BEB0FCCAF840" box="[717,887,1978,2005]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="35">Centris bicolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is relatively widely distributed, and according to these authors, in 
<collectingCountry id="9BEA7644BC4AFFD8502BBED5FE24F86C" box="[341,409,2014,2040]" name="Brazil" pageId="12" pageNumber="35">Brazil</collectingCountry>
can also be found in the states of 
<collectingRegion id="2139F836BC4AFFD85268BED5FCE7F86C" box="[790,858,2014,2040]" country="Brazil" name="Bahia" pageId="12" pageNumber="35">Bahia</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="2139F836BC4AFFD8521BBED5FC43F86C" box="[869,1022,2014,2040]" country="Brazil" name="Minas Gerais" pageId="12" pageNumber="35">Minas Gerais</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="2139F836BC4AFFD85577BED5FBE8F86C" box="[1033,1109,2014,2040]" country="Brazil" name="Parana" pageId="12" pageNumber="35">Paraná</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion id="2139F836BC4AFFD855F2BED5FABDF86C" box="[1164,1280,2014,2040]" country="Brazil" name="Sao Paulo" pageId="12" pageNumber="35">São Paulo</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
